<TITLE> Inqilab Khulna bureau chief gets 4 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, May 28 (bdnews24.com)- A Khulna court Monday sentenced Khulna bureau chief of Dainik Inqilab ATM Rafique to four-year rigorous imprisonment. The court also ordered that he pay a Tk 10,000 fine, in default of which, he would have to suffer RI for another three months. The metropolitan magistrate of Khulna Speedy Trial Tribunal, Atiqul Haque, handed down the verdict. Joint forces, according to the case proceedings, caught journalist ATM Rafique in the act of taking Tk 20,000 in bribe at the local Inqilab bureau office on April 10 from Sunderbans forest unit ranger Yunus Ali and deputy ranger Syed Mahmud Ullah. The same night forest officer Yunus Ali filed a case against Rafique. The investigating officer of the case Sonadanga thana sub-inspector SM Obaidul Haque submitted a chargesheet against Rafique on April 19 to court. Charges were framed on April 22. The court pronounced the verdict after examining 15 witnesses. bdnews2
